content: Updated "Add details" button in pending trades page to pass trade data via URL parameters. Modified the Link href in finalization trades section to pass trade.needs as requested and trade.offers as exchange parameters, ensuring consistency with messages page implementation.

Moved TradeRequestInfo component in add-details page to span full width across both columns. Component is now positioned above the two-column layout (form fields + textarea) instead of being constrained to the left column only.

Fixed messages page viewport layout to prevent scrolling. Set container height to calc(100vh - 140px) to account for navbar, added paddingBottom 20px for spacing, and used useEffect to set body overflow hidden to prevent page scrolling. Messages container is now fixed within viewport.

Fixed messages container viewport height constraints. Changed messages page from min-h-screen to h-screen, adjusted content height to h-[calc(100vh-120px)] for proper navbar spacing, added max-h-full and overflow-hidden to MessageConversation and MessageList components to prevent overflow beyond viewport height.

Made TradeRequestInfo card bigger by increasing padding (px-8 py-6), text sizes (18px labels, 15px pill text), spacing (gap-8, mb-2 for labels), pill padding (px-15 py-8), and border radius (20px outer, 18px pills). Card is now more prominent and visually larger on the add-details page.

Made TradeRequestInfo component dynamic by passing trade data via URL parameters. Modified "Add details" button in message-conversation to pass requested/exchange data as URL params. Updated add-details page to read URL parameters using useSearchParams and display the actual conversation's trade data instead of hardcoded values. Added conditional rendering to only show component when trade data is available.

Moved TradeRequestInfo component to align with the left column in add-details page. Component is now positioned inside the left column div (width 400px) above the delivery mode selection, instead of spanning full width above both columns.

Created TradeRequestInfo component and added it to the add-details page. The component displays "Requested" and "In exchange for" sections with blue and purple pill-shaped containers respectively, matching the design from the messages page. Component is now positioned above the delivery mode selection on the /home/trades/add-details page.
